	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Oh, and by the way, a normal two-handed hammer is 13/51 so if you're looking for a weapon with a high dam/sec ratio, you are better with this as it is easier to get and a does not involve traipsing around all over Norrath to get it. If you are looking for a magic weapon to hit magic only mobs, then there are many other shorter quests available in both Qeynos and Kaladim to get one. I mean think about it, if you are a young, melee or healer type who can use this thing, you will have to get ported back and forth at an expense of at least 20PP both ways or 10PP if you have gate and are brave enough to leave your bind point so far behind and if you are of a high enough level to survive walking all the way between Kaladim and Qeynos twice, or you can teleport yourself, then you probably already have or can easily get something better. Besides, with all the high levels selling cool stuff, why waste time questing for this piece of crap. Did you ever notice that the payoff for doing quests in this game is rarely worth the time invested and sometimes the bad faction hits you might take along the way? 
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
