	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The faction that you ruin by killing Trumpy or the Rat Misk is Corrupt Qeynos Guards. When a corrupt attacks you, the regular guards will also jump in the assumption being that the guard must have a reason for attacking you and they don't know that the guard is corrupt. To check your con with the guard factions, con Corporal Lancot, who is often found at the gate or the Temple of Life or somewhere in between. He is a good guard. If your faction with the good guards is bad, kill gnolls until it is at least amiable. Also con Lt. Dagarok who usually stands around the corner from Sneed Galliways near the pond. He is a corrupt guard. He wanders off from time to time and sometimes even despawns but he always returns to this spot. If you have high faction with Guards of Qeynos (the good ones), try doing the evil version of the quest where you deliver the box from guard Weleth to Nesiff Talaherd and deliver the invoice to Lt Dagarok instead of Weleth. This gives Corrupt Guards faction. Also, buying honeymeads for Trumpy Irontoe before you kill him builds up Corrupt Guards faction, just run outside after each faction hit and con one of the two stationary guards (they're both good) at the entrance to the dock to make sure you aren't indifferent (or worse) to them. If you are, go out and kill more gnolls to bring it back up to amiable. You MUST have high faction with the legit guards before you attempt to build faction with the corrupt ones as this lowers your faction with the legit ones. Keeping your faction with the good ones high by killing gnolls when necessary prevents the reverse situation where the evil guards love you and the good ones want to remove your innards with a rusty spoon.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
