				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				There is nothing hard about killing Trumpy. I am a level 12 barbarian shaman and I had no troubles at all after a friend told me about the quest. He told me to mention Sragg. I went into Fish's Ale(the bar trupmy and his pals hang out in) and he was there at the counter. I hailed him and said who is sragg? He then said somethign about not knowing anything about Sragg and he left the bar. I followed him for a little while..did a quick check to make sure there were no guards around. What is weird is he has dual wield(for a level  5) rusty daggers. I did not root or snare..since I had no spell. I beat him down pretty good..he started running..the normal guards of Qeynos have no problem if you kill him as I was standing next to one and killing him. I was actually pretty close to the bar and none of his friend tried to kill me. The only tough friend he had was Bruno Barstomper or something like that..al the others were green to me. Anyways I killed him and got his head...I believe it spawns on him everytime. I am currently on my way to get to Faydwer. I stopped in the Karanas to do some bandit hunting...exp is good and bandit sashes are nice to heh..well..this is all I know about the quest except I have to give it to some Dwarf in Kaladim named like Byzar or something. Hope this helps.<BR>
